evelopment, and deployment of our satellite constellations, launch vehicles, ground stations... AI compute infrastructure, data centers, and other supporting infrastructure."\n*   In the notes to the financial statements, it mentions that "Construction in progress is primarily comprised of ongoing construction and expansion of the facilities and equipment as well as AI infrastructure that has not yet been placed in service."\n*   It states that "Interest is capitalized during the construction period for significant long term construction projects, such as the AI infrastructure data centers and launch facilities."\n*   It mentions recording "impairment charges of $24 million related to the write off of damaged flight vehicles in the Space segment," which implies that flight vehicles are treated as capitalized assets subject to impairment. \n\nWhile this implies a capital expenditure model for these assets, the provided text does not contain an explicit accounting policy statement declaring whether the *future* orbital AI compute satellites will be capitalized or expensed once deployed.',
